.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "Holberton School" "_printf manual"

.SH NAME
_printf - custom implementation of printf

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function produces output according to a format string.

It writes output to the standard output (stdout). The format string
can contain normal characters and format specifiers that begin with '%'.

Supported format specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.

.TP
.B %d
Prints a decimal integer.

.TP
.B %i
Prints an integer.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful return, _printf returns the number of characters printed
(excluding the null byte).

If an error occurs, a negative value is returned.

.SH EXAMPLE
.B _printf("Hello %s\n", "World");

